.
(10) Others
In case We wish to use your personal
						information for any purpose not disclosed in this Policy, We will inform you of
						the new purpose by updating the privacy policy or other means, and obtain your
						consent or meet other Legality Basis.
2.2
Retention
							period of personal information
The retention of personal information is
						influenced by various factors, such as the type and processing purpose of
						personal information, our legal obligations, and provision of defense for
						existing or anticipated legal proceedings.
Normally, to the extent permitted by the
						applicable laws and regulations, We only retain your personal information for
						the period necessary for providing Our Services and achieving the
						above-mentioned purposes. We will also retain your personal information when
						necessary to fulfill contractual and legal obligations, safeguard our
						legitimate business interests, and make demands, legal claims, or defenses.
In case you violate our agreement, terms,
						or guidelines, We may immediately remove your personal profile information (including
						profile picture, and nickname) and user-generated contents from public view;
						provided that We may retain such information in the backend for handling your
						violation.
When the retention period expires, We will
						promptly erase or anonymize your personal information, unless otherwise
						required by the applicable laws and regulations. In case your personal
						information cannot be immediately erased or anonymized due to legal
						requirements or technical limitations, We will securely store your personal
						information, ensure that your personal information will not be processed in any
						other way, and promptly erase or anonymize your personal information after the
						limitations are lifted.
3
How
							do We disclose your personal information to third parties
We will not sell your personal
							information. Under the following circumstances, We may share, entrust the
							processing of, transfer, or otherwise disclose your personal information to the
							necessary extent.
3.1
Sharing
							with affiliates of IQIYI Group
As an international group, Our Services
						may be provided by or with the assistance from affiliated companies of IQIYI
						Group, so as to achieve our commercial operations. They will process the
						information proactively provided by you, information automatically collected by
						us, and information from third parties for us to provide necessary functions
						such as R&D, storage, security, content delivery, analysis and statistics,
						customer and technical support, and service optimization and improvement.
3.2
Sharing
							with third-party partners
To the extent required for implementing
						the corresponding services, We may share your personal information with the
						following types of third-party partners.
(1) Third-party platform partners
Some services provided by third-party
						platform partners may be integrated into our platform, such as
						registration/login of account, and sharing of audio/video contents. When you
						use Our Services while also using the services of third-party platform partners
						integrated into our platform, We will share the
information automatically
							collected by us (such as device information, and cookie information)
with
						such third-party platform partners, so as to achieve a smooth usage experience
						for you.
(2) Payment service partners
When you purchase our membership benefits
						and use third-party payment services, We will share with the payment service
						providers the
information proactively provided by you (such as personal
							profile information, and payment information) and
information
							automatically collected by us (such as device information, and cookie
							information)
, so as to process your order, complete your payment process,
						and ensure the security of the transaction.
(3) Operational partners
We may carry out joint marketing events
						with third parties and share
event information (such as contact information,
							and
delivery
								address
)
with operational partners during joint
						marketing events, so as to enable them to promptly distribute prizes/gifts to
						you.
(4) Advertisement partners (including
							advertisers, advertisement service providers, advertisement evaluation
							companies, and other partners)
Advertisement services are an important
						source of revenue for us to maintain the operation of our platform. Our
						advertisement partners may collect some of your personal information through
						our platform, or We may share with them the
information a
utomatically
							collected by us (such as advertisement information, device information,
							location information, speculation information, and cookie information)
, so
						as to achieve better advertisement display effects, recommend personalized advertisements
						to you, promote your interaction with advertisements, and evaluate and improve
						our advertisement effectiveness. However, please rest assured that the above-mentioned
						advertisement partners will not collect your watching record information on our
						platform.
Specifically, in our advertisement
						business collaboration with Liveramp, We will provide privacy protection
						identifiers to Liveramp, so as to better showcase suitable advertisement
						content to you. In case you want to exit, please complete the setting through
https://liveramp.com/opt_out/
.
(5) Promotion partners
For the purpose of conducting marketing,
						We may engage third-party platforms to promote Our Products and/or Services.
						The agents which cooperate with us, the service providers which provide the
						promotion platforms, and the service providers which evaluate and optimize the
						promotion results (collectively referred to as "
Promotion Partners
")
						may, through us, collect or access the
information automatically collected
							by us (such as advertisement information, device information, location
							information
,
speculative
information,
and cookie information)
.
						However, please rest assured that the above-mentioned Promotion Partners will
						not collect your watching record information on our platform.
3.3
Entrusted
							processing by third parties
We may entrust service providers to
						represent or assist us in providing services to you, so as to support the
						development, operation, and improvement of Our Products and/or Services. The
						services provided by them will include IT and infrastructure services, customer
						service, marketing services, research, analysis and statistics, security risk
						control, and service optimization and improvement. The service providers will
						only act as data processor, and will be entrusted to process the personal
						information required for provision of their services.
3.4
Change
							of control of similar transactions
In case We engage
						in merger, acquisition, reorganization, spin off, bankruptcy, asset transfers
						or similar transactions, and your personal information may be transferred as
						part of such transactions, We will notify you in accordance with the applicable
						laws and regulations and make every effort to require the new data controller
						to continue to comply with and fulfill all the contents of this Policy.
3.5
Disclose
							to public authorities
Under certain circumstances, in accordance
						with the applicable laws and regulations or the requirements of public
						authorities (including administrative agencies, judicial agencies, other
						regulatory agencies, and designated third parties), We may disclose your
						personal information to public authorities, so as to comply with and fulfill
						the obligations and procedures under applicable laws and regulations, and
						protect the legitimate rights and interests of you, us, our users, the public,
						or other third parties. In accordance with the applicable laws and regulations,
						or the valid legal procedural documents such as subpoenas, court orders, or
						search warrants, such disclosure may be made with or without your consent, or
						with or without notice, and We are generally prohibited from notifying you of
						such disclosure.
3.6
Public
							availability within platform
We are committed to enhancing the
						interaction experience between users and other users when using Our Services.
						Your
personal
							profile information (profile picture, and nickname) and user-generated contents
							(such as comments on TV episodes)
will be publicly
						displayed on our platform, and other users (including visitor users) can see
						such information.
4
Cross-border
							transfer of personal information
At
							present, our data center is located in Singapore, and We will transfer the
							collected personal information of you to our data center in Singapore for
							centralized storage and subsequent processing. In addition, IQIYI Group's
							affiliated companies and our third-party partners may be granted remote access
							to some of your personal information, or We may transfer some of your personal
							information to the countries/regions where the data centers of IQIYI Group's
							affiliated companies and third-party partners are located.
Some or all of the above-mentioned
							entities may be located outside of your country/region, and the applicable
							local data protection laws may differ from those in your country/region.
However,
						We will ensure that the transfer of such personal information complies with the
						applicable data protection laws and this Policy. In addition, We will adopt the
						measures at organizational, technical, and protocol levels, so as to maintain
						the security of such transfer and ensure that the personal information is
						adequately protected after cross-border transfer.
5
Security
							of personal information
We have adopted the security technology
						measures that comply with the applicable data protection laws and industrial
						standards, as well as the supporting protection measures at multiple levels
						such as organizational structures and management systems to protect the
						security of your personal information, in order to minimize the risks of
						leakage, damage, misuse, unauthorized access, unauthorized disclosure, and
						alteration of personal information (hereinafter referred to as "
Data
							Security Incidents
"). The relevant information security management
						system involved in IQIYI's services has passed ISO/IEC 27001, ISO/IEC 29151,
						ISO/IEC 27701, and PCI DSS certifications. Our specific protection measures include:
(1) Technical measures
We have adopted the cryptographic
						techniques such as transport-layer security protocols to prevent the risk of
						transmission links being sniffed, eavesdropped, or intercepted; We have adopted
						the secure storage measures such as data classification and hierarchical
						disposal; We have strictly controlled the data permissions and adopted the
						multiple identity authentication technologies; We have monitored the processing
						of data, so as to monitor and audit the entire lifecycle of data.
(2) Organizational and management
							measures
We have established a dedicated department
						for protection of personal information, responsible for the protection personal
						information and the exercise of data subject rights; We have established the
						internal control management systems such as business data security usage
						standards, data cooperation standards management systems; We have minimized the
						permissions for authorized employees; We have regularly organized the employee
						training on information security protection; We have locked the personal
						information storage area and restricted employees’ access to such storage area.
(3) Emergency response to security
							incidents
We have set up an IQIYI Security Emergency
						Response Center, which has developed multiple security management systems and
						emergency response plans, clarifying the reporting and emergency response
						procedures for security incidents. In case a personal information security
						incident unfortunately occurs, We will immediately initiate the emergency plan,
						minimize the impact of the security incident, and prevent the expansion of
						security incident. We will inform you of security incidents by means such as phone
						calls, push notifications, announcements, and emails in accordance with the applicable
						data protection laws.
6
Your
							personal information rights and ways to exercise them
6.1
Your
							rights to personal information
You
							have the rights to your personal information as specified by applicable laws
							and regulations, which usually include the following types. However, the
							regulations may vary in different countries/regions, and the types and
							conditions of your rights under applicable laws and regulations may differ.
(1) Right
							to know
You
						have the right to know about our processing of your personal information.
We have
						specifically formulated and published this Policy to inform you how We process
						and protect your personal information. You can also contact us and request
						further information or explanation.
(2) Access
							right
You
						have the right to confirm with us whether We have processed your personal
						information, and you have the right to access, query, and copy your personal
						information held by us.
You can
						access and query some of your personal information at any time by logging into
						your IQIYI account. You can also contact us to request access, query, or copying
						of more of your personal information, and We will provide you with a copy of
						your personal information in electronic form.
(3) Right
							to correction
You
						have the right to request us to correct, supplement, or update any inaccurate,
						incomplete, or expired personal information related to you.
You can
						correct some of your personal information (such as your account information) at
						any time by logging into your IQIYI account. You can also contact us to request
						correction, supplementation, or update of your personal information.
(4) Portability
							right
Under
						specific circumstances specified by the applicable laws and regulations (such
						as when the Legality Basis for processing of personal information is your
						consent or
necessity for conclusion or performance of a contract between you
							and us
), you have the right to request us to provide your personal
						information in a structured, commonly-used and machine-readable format, and to
						transfer your personal information to other data controllers designated by you.
You can
						contact us to request the exercise of data portability rights.
(5) Right
							to erase
Under
						specific circumstances specified by the applicable laws and regulations, you
						have the right to request us to erase your personal information, such as when
						the processing purpose has been achieved, when you withdraw your consent and
						there is no other Legality Basis, or when the processing activity is illegal.
						However, if, in accordance with the applicable laws and regulations, We must or
						have legitimate reasons to retain your personal information, We may continue to
						retain such personal information.
You can
						erase some of your personal information at any time by logging into your IQIYI
						account. You can also contact us to request the erasure of more of your
						personal information. However, please note that, erasing personal information
						may affect our ability to provide the corresponding features or services
						normally.
In
						accordance with the applicable laws and regulations, We will promptly erase or
						anonymize your personal information. In case your personal information cannot
						be immediately erased or anonymized due to legal requirements or technical
						limitations, We will securely store your personal information, ensure that your
						personal information will not be processed in any other way, and promptly erase
						or anonymize your personal information after the limitations are lifted.
(6)
							Right to restrict processing
Under
						specific circumstances specified by the applicable laws and regulations, you
						have the right to restrict our processing of some or all of your personal
						information, such as when there is a dispute over the accuracy of personal
						information.
You can
						contact us to request suspension of processing of your personal information.
(7) Right
							to object
Under
						specific circumstances specified by the applicable laws and regulations, you
						have the right to object to our processing of your personal information, such
						as when the Legality Basis for processing of personal information is legitimate
						interests or public interests.
You can
						contact us to request that We stop processing your personal information for
						specific purposes.
You
						have the right to refuse to receive our marketing information and personalized
						recommendations, as detailed in Sections 6.1(10) - (11) hereof.
(8) Consent
							and withdrawal of consent
For processing activities based on your
						consent as a Legality Basis, you have the right to independently decide whether
						to give consent for our processing of your personal information in accordance
						with this Policy, and have the right to withdraw your consent at any time.
You can withdraw your consent for certain
						processing activities at any time by logging into your IQIYI account and using
						the online-provided function buttons (such as disabling personalized contents,
						and personalized advertisements). You can also contact us to withdraw your
						consent.
After you withdraw your consent, We will
						no longer process your personal information and may therefore be unable to
						continue providing you with the corresponding services. In addition, the
						processing activities already carried out by us based on your consent before
						your withdrawal of consent will remain valid and unaffected.
(9) Right
							not to be bound by automatically-made decisions
You have the right not to be bound by
						decisions made solely based on automated processing behavior, including user
						profiling, in case such decisions will have legal or similar significant
						impacts on you.
We may analyze your preferences and
						recommend personalized contents and advertisements to you. You can disable
						personalized recommendations at any time, as detailed in Sections 2.1(5) and
						6.1(10) hereof.
In case We involve more automated
						decision-making in the future (including user profiling), you can contact us to
						request exemption from
automatically-made decisions.
(10) Disabling
							personalized recommendations
The
						contents and advertisements displayed to you on our platform may be
						personalized recommendations based on your preferences. In case you no longer
						want to receive personalized contents and advertisements, you can disable them
						at any time within the application through the following path:
l
Personalized
						Contents: "My - Settings - Privacy - Privacy Settings - Enable
						Personalized Contents";
l
Personalized
						Advertisements: "My - Settings - Privacy - Privacy Settings - Enable
						Personalized Advertisements".
After you
						disable personalized recommendations, you will still see the advertisements and
						contents randomly recommended by us, but you may miss out on some exciting
						contents that interests you and some advertisement information that is more
						attractive to you.
(11) Unsubscribing
You have the right to reject our marketing
						information at any time.
For the marketing emails and messages send
						by us to you, you can unsubscribe from our marketing promotions and information
						by clicking on the "unsubscribe" link therein or following other
						instructions provided by us. For other forms of marketing information, please
						contact us via
privacy@iq.com
to unsubscribe.
(12) Disabling
							message notification
We may send you information about Our Products
						and/or Services through push notifications, internal messages, and other forms,
						including membership benefits, promotions, and launches/updates of film and
						television episodes. In case you do not wish to receive such message
						notifications, you can disable the message notification function by clicking on
						"My - Settings - Privacy Settings - Enable Message Notifications".
(13) Cookie
							settings
For the cookies and other similar
						technologies used by us, please refer to our
Cookie Policy
, for information
						on how to change cookie settings.
(14) Complaints
							and lawsuit
In case you believe that We have violated
						the applicable laws and regulations during processing of your personal
						information, you have the right to file a complaint with the data protection
						agency or file a lawsuit with the court.
6.2
Exercise
							and response of rights
You
						will not suffer any discrimination due to exercise of your rights.
You can
						contact us via
privacy@qiyi.com
to exercise your rights or consult about exercise of your rights. In addition,
						you can exercise your rights more conveniently through the online functions
						provided by us, as described above.
We will
						respond to your exercise request promptly within a reasonable time in
						accordance with the applicable laws and regulations.
In order to ensure
							security, We may need to verify your identity before responding to your
							exercise request.
We usually do not charge any fees for your reasonable
						requests. However, for excessive, repetitive, or unreasonable exercise
						requests, We may charge fees or refuse your request at our discretion.
Please
							be aware that, your rights are not absolute. Sometimes, in accordance with the
							applicable laws and regulations, your rights may be subject to certain
							conditions or limitations
, such as national security, public
						security and interests, prevention and investigation of crime, and protection
						of others’ legitimate rights and interests. In case We are unable to fully or
						partially respond to your exercise request, We will explain the reason to you.
						In case the applicable laws and regulations in your country/region do not
						support specific types of rights, or in case there are additional applicable
						conditions or limitations, We will also inform you.
7
Protection
							of minors
Our
							Services are primarily aimed at adults rather than minors.
In
							principle, you must be at least 18 years old to use Our Services.
In case
						the age limit for adults in your country/region is higher than 18 years old,
						the regulations in your country/region shall prevail.
We
						attach great importance to the protection of personal information of minors.
Minors
							shall read this Policy with the accompaniment and guidance of their legal
							guardians, and may use IQIYI services under the supervision of their legal
							guardians only after reading and accepting this Policy.
8
Application
								and update of this Policy
8.1
Scope
							of application
Some of Our Services may be provided
						through third-party platforms, or use the functions operated by third-party
						platforms, or include or link to the websites or services operated by
						third-party platforms. The personal information processing rules of such third
						parties are determined by themselves and may differ from ours. The websites,
						applications, platforms, and other products or services of third parties have
						their respective independent privacy policies.
This Policy is not applicable
							to any product or service provided by any third party. Therefore, before using
							any product or service of any third party,
you are advised to
							carefully and attentively read the privacy policy published by such third party
							through its website, application, or platform, and understand the processing by
							such third party of your personal information.
8.2
Update
In accordance with
							the applicable laws and regulations and in light of the development of Our
							Services, We may update and publish this Policy from time to time, and notify you
							thereof in accordance with the provisions of the applicable data protection
							laws, by means such as (without limitation) notification, push message, pop-up
							and email.
In case you continue to use Our
							Services after the updated version of this Policy takes effect, you will be
							deemed as having accepted such update. In case you do not accept the update to
							this Policy, you may stop using Our Services, including canceling your IQIYI
							account.
Please refer to the top of the page for
						the latest update time of this Policy.
You can always view the latest version of
						this Policy through the following path: "My - Settings - Privacy - Privacy
						Policy".
