									on how users use Our Services, and to improve and optimize Our Services)
(9)
Compliance
									with applicable laws and regulations and performance of
IQIYI Service
										Agreement
and
IQIYI VIP Member Service Agreement
Processing is
									necessary for performance of the legal obligations of the data controller;
Processing is
									necessary for performance of the contract to which the Data Subject is a
									party, or necessary for implementation of the actions requested by the Data
									Subject prior to the conclusion of contract
2.
Cross-border
							transfer of personal information
When We transfer your personal information
						to countries/regions outside the EEA, the UK, or Switzerland, We will use the
						following cross-border transfer tools to ensure the full protection of your
						personal information:
(1)
Sufficiency
							Determination.
In accordance with Article 45 of the
General Data
							Protection Regulation
(
GDPR
) of the European Union, personal
						information can be transferred to a third country or international organization
						when the European Commission determines that such third country, a region or
						one or more specific sectors of such third country, or such international
						organization has met the sufficient protection standards. Such transfer does
						not require any special authorization. We will, in accordance with the
						above-mentioned terms, transfer some of your personal information collected by
						us as described in this Policy to those third parties located in
						countries/regions which have obtained the above-mentioned sufficiency
						determination.
(2)
Standard
							Contractual Terms
. In accordance with Article 46 of GDPR,
						standard contractual terms are one of the appropriate protection measures
						approved by the European Commission and have also been approved by the UK and
						Switzerland.
In case the destination of the transfer has not obtained
						the above-mentioned sufficiency determination, We will sign the standard
						contractual terms with the data recipient (including affiliated companies of
						IQIYI Group) (with respect to the UK, We will simultaneously sign the UK
						appendix), and then transfer your personal information across borders
						accordingly. You can contact us through the contact information in Chapter 9
						hereof to request a copy of the standard contractual terms.
3.
Protection
							of minors
In the EEA, the
						UK, and Switzerland, you must be at least 18 years old to use Our Services.
The US
1.
Collection and use of personal information
The types
						of personal information collected by us from you in the past 12 months are
						detailed in Section 1.1 hereof.
Depending
						on how and to what extent you use Our Services, the types of personal
						information actually collected and used may vary (such as, in case you have not
						purchased VIP membership services, We will not collect or use your payment
						information), as detailed in Section 2.1 hereof.
You can
						also contact us through the contact information in Chapter 9 hereof to obtain
						more information.
In certain
						states (such as California), the following personal information may constitute
						sensitive personal information: your IQIYI account number and account
						verification information (password or verification code), your bank card
						number, CVV, and expiration date information. For the using purpose of
						sensitive personal information and disclosure to third parties, please refer to
						Section 2.1 and Chapter 3 hereof.
In certain
						states (such as Virginia), the processing of your sensitive personal
						information requires your consent. However, We have not collected or processed
						any sensitive personal information under the applicable data protection laws in
						Virginia.
2.
Disclosure (including sharing) of personal
							information
The types
						of your personal information disclosed by us to third parties in the past 12
						months (including sharing for cross-scenario advertisement purposes) are
						detailed in Chapter 3 hereof (in conjunction with Section 1.1 hereof).
						Depending on how and to what extent you use Our Services, the types of personal
						information actually disclosed may vary (such as, in case you do not use
						third-party payment services, We will not disclose your payment information).
						You can also contact us through the contact information in Chapter 9 hereof to
						obtain more information.
We will not "sell" your personal
						information for monetary or other valuable consideration.
We also will not share the personal information
						of minors aged 18 or below.
For the
						avoidance of doubt, “Sell,” “selling,” “sale,” or “sold,’’ means selling,
						renting, releasing, disclosing, disseminating, making available, transferring,
						or otherwise communicating orally, in writing, or by electronic or other means,
						a consumer’s personal information by the business to a third party for monetary
						or other valuable consideration.
3.
Your
							personal information rights
In addition to the
						types of rights listed in Chapter 7 hereof, you also have the following rights
						over your personal information, subject to the limitations of the applicable
						data protection laws in each state.
l
Limiting Our Use and Disclosure of Your Sensitive Personal Information
: You have
the
right
to
limit
							our use and disclosure of your sensitive personal information to
the
extent necessary
for provision of
Our
							Services to you.
l
Opt Out:
You have
the
right
to
demand
that
We cease
the
following actions,
and
We will
							stop
them
at
							your request, unless you authorize us
to
continue
							such actions:
o
Selling or sharing your personal information to
						or with third parties for cross-scenario advertisement activities;
o
Cross-platform and personalized targeted advertisement.
Request
							by Proxy
: In case you are
a
US state resident
who
has
the
right
to
use
an
authorized
							proxy, you can use
the
authorized proxy
to
make
an
exercise
							request for you.
The a
uthorized proxy can
							submit request on your behalf to us, accompanied by a statement proving his/her
							authority to act on your behalf as per our requirements. Please note that,
							verifying and fulfilling the request submitted by your proxy may require
							additional time. Once confirmed, your authorized proxy may exercise your rights
							on your behalf, subject to the requirements of the applicable laws and
							regulations.
Appeal
: When We reject
						your exercise request, in case you are a resident of a US state who has the
						right to appeal our exercise decision,
you may appeal our decision regarding your personal information exercise
							request to us.
When
								you submit your appeal request, please use the same email address or other
								contact information as when you first submitted your exercise request, so that
								We can connect your appeal with your initial exercise request. Meanwhile,
								please attach supporting documents or information regarding your appeal.
4.
Protection
							of minors
In the US (unless
						specific states have special regulations), you must be at least 18 years old to
						use Our Services.